ecological_assessment.qualitative_description: The model captures most NPZ model characteristics with significant complexity and additional nuanced temperature and light dependencies

nutrient_equation_uptake.explanation: Uses Michaelis-Menten kinetics (N/(K_N+N)) with temperature and light scaling. Includes nutrient uptake efficiency (eta), but lacks explicit self-shading term a/(b+c*P)

nutrient_equation_recycling.explanation: Includes remineralization (r_D * D) but lacks explicit zooplankton recycling terms (beta*lambda*P^2/(mu^2+P^2)*Z and gamma*q*Z)

nutrient_equation_mixing.explanation: No explicit environmental mixing term k*(N0-N)

phytoplankton_equation_growth.explanation: Captures nutrient-limited growth with temperature and light scaling. Uses N/(K_N+N) and includes additional efficiency factors

phytoplankton_equation_loss.explanation: Includes mortality (m_P * P), predation (grazing), and additional sinking terms. Lacks direct match to lambda*P^2/(mu^2+P^2)*Z

zooplankton_equation.explanation: Captures zooplankton growth through predation and mortality with temperature and nutrient dependencies. Differs from exact lambda formulation
